channel.title: Unable to find the model..?
channel.description: Okay so my client has the new whip model and i'm trying to get the old whip model. In the beginning I just tried to delete the whip ints from class 8.java and I deleted 5409 and 5412 from the models, compiled, and ran.. but the new whip model was still there.. so i searched around and i heard it could be gzipped so I maybe had to put a new model or something.. So I downloaded the old whip model (2 dat files, 5409 and 5412) and i got the ints.. i copied/pasted the ints into class 8.java and i copied/pasted the 2 dat files into my Models folder in the client.. compiled, ran.. and when i log into my server and try to add the models "Add model 5409" or "Add model 5412".. I get the message saying "Unable to find the model. 5409".. I have no idea why it says its unable to find the model when its sitting right there in my models folder..?

item.title: Unable to find the model..?
item.dc:creator: @tanner1234 tanner1234
item.description:
@tanner1234 wrote:

Okay so my client has the new whip model and i’m trying to get the old whip model. In the beginning I just tried to delete the whip ints from class 8.java and I deleted 5409 and 5412 from the models, compiled, and ran… but the new whip model was still there… so i searched around and i heard it could be gzipped so I maybe had to put a new model or something… So I downloaded the old whip model (2 dat files, 5409 and 5412) and i got the ints… i copied/pasted the ints into class 8.java and i copied/pasted the 2 dat files into my Models folder in the client… compiled, ran… and when i log into my server and try to add the models “Add model 5409” or “Add model 5412”… I get the message saying “Unable to find the model. 5409”… I have no idea why it says its unable to find the model when its sitting right there in my models folder…?
